#Here I assume you just installed you Debian system using the process given in the readme.

Begin by setting up your system:

su 
apt-get install git sudo

#add yourself to sudoers
sudo usermod -a -G sudo <username>

#setup your git 
git config --global user.name "<your name>"
git config --global user.email <your email>
clone https://github.com/Sebbestune/DebConf.git
cd DebConf

Run the script
./auto_config

This will take a while...

Next if you want to do Android or Mobile development do the next part manually. 

./xinit-i3

#Download Command line tools only (for example by using firefox) from: https://developer.android.com/studio it should be called something like sdk-tools-linux-*.zip (example: sdk-tools-linux-4333796.zip)
#After this you might stay in i3wm and for example create a new terminal instance, or quit from i3wm and continue in the terminal. Either way do the following commands or execute the android_install_script. 

./android_sdk_install

#or

cd 
cd Downloads/
unzip sdk-tools
rm sdk-tools-linux-*.zip
sudo mv tools /opt/android-tools
cd 
printf "\nexport PATH=/opt/android-tools/:/opt/android-tools/bin:$PATH\n" | tee -a .profile
touch .android/repositories.cfg
sdkmanager --no_https --list

#Now you're all done!
